modules.description: This module provides infix operators for transforming and combining signal values. It works with reactive signals, allowing functions to be applied directly to signal streams. Concrete use cases include mapping values over signals, zipping multiple signals, and applying function signals to value signals.

This module provides reactive signal management through creation, value updates, subscription control, and derived signal transformations, supporting operations like `map`, `filter`, and `sample` to handle dynamic data flows. It works with temporal data structures that track changing values over time, enabling efficient propagation of updates in scenarios like state synchronization, event-driven systems, or real-time UIs where selective notifications and batched changes minimize redundant computations.
